<item>
            <title>[CAMEL-920] file component consumer.regexPattern does not work as expected (matching is applied not only to file, but also to directory)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-920</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;file component consumer.regexPattern does not work as expected&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;example : from(&quot;file://d:/the_input_dir?consumer.regexPattern=.*\.xml$&quot;.to(whatever)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(should match only files, that has extention .xml)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the result of the above regexPattern is, that no file will be proccessed, regardless if an existing filename matches the pattern.&lt;br/&gt;
FileConsumer.pollFileOrDirectory() applies the regexPattern on the starting directory (the_input_dir) which will not match.&lt;/p&gt;



</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows XP, JDK 1.5, Apache Camel 1.5 Snapshot&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
